15 NEW SECTION. Section 14. Cattle assessment adjustment -- referendum. (1) (a) A referendum
16 must be held every 5 years. Cattle sellers may petition the department for a referendum to repeal or change the
17 cattle assessment amount with a petition collecting the signatures of at least 10% of cattle sellers who have
18 paid in the current or previous calendar year the assessment collected under [section 12].
19 (b) The petition process must be completed within 1 year of the date of filing the petition with the
20 department.
21 (2) All referendums must be conducted in accordance with [section 11(2) through (5)].
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 15. Penalty for nonpayment. A cattle seller who fails to pay the cattle
24 assessment pursuant to [sections 2 through 16] is subject to a penalty of 5% of the amount of the assessment
25 determined to be due, as provided in [sections 2 through 16], plus 1% of that amount for each month of delay or
26 the fraction of that amount after the expiration of the month after the assessment became due. The penalty
27 must be paid to the department and disposed of as provided in [section 10].
